      <h2>NHS Complaints</h2>

      <p class="lead">NHS Board Contacts</p>
      <p>Should you wish to raise a complaint or discuss an ongoing complaint then please click on the following link showing contact details for all <a href="/Health-Topics/Quality-Indicators/NHS-Complaints-Statistics/Contacts-and-Links/Board-Contacts-201415.xlsx">NHS Boards</a> </p>
      
      <p class="lead">Scottish Public Service Ombudsman</p>
      <p>This site outlines the role and remit of the Ombudsman, which replaces the Health Services Commissioner.</p>
      <p><a href="http://www.spso.org.uk/">www.spso.org.uk</a></p>
        
      <p class="lead">Patient Advice and Support Service (PASS)</p>
      <p><a href="http://www.cas.org.uk/patientadvice" >Patient Advice and Support Service</a>: Independent service delivered by the Scottish Citizens Advice Bureau (CAB) Service that raises awareness of patients/public rights and responsibilities when using health services.  PASS supports patients and the public to give feedback, comments, raise concerns or make complaints.</p>
      
      <p class="lead">Healthcare Improvement Scotland</p>
      <p>Healthcare Improvement Scotland is a health body formed on the 1 April 2011, which has the focus and key responsibility to help NHS Scotland and independent healthcare providers deliver high quality, evidence-based, safe, effective and person-centred care; and to scrutinise services to provide public assurance about the quality and safety of that care.</p>
      <p><a href="http://www.healthcareimprovementscotland.org/">www.healthcareimprovementscotland.org</a></p>
      
      <p class="lead">Department of Health</p>
      <p><a href="http://www.hscic.gov.uk/catalogue/PUB18021">Data on written complaints in the NHS 2014-15, England, published 26 August 2015</a></p>
      
      <p class="lead">Northern Ireland</p>
      <p>Northern Ireland have an integrated health and social health care system, which mean that Trusts figures include complaints regarding social workers, Scottish figures do not include social workers.</p>
      <p><a href="http://www.hscboard.hscni.net/publications/Complaints/">Further information on the Northern Irish complaints system</a></p>
      
      <p class="lead">Welsh Assembly Government</p>
      <p><a href="http://wales.gov.uk/docs/statistics/2014/140609-nhs-complaints-data-collection-termination-en.pdf">NHS Wales no longer collects data on complaints</a></p>
      <p><a href="http://wales.gov.uk/statistics-and-research/complaints-nhs/?lang=en">The last Complaints report for NHS in Wales, 2010/11, was published on 21 September 2011</a></p>
      <p>If you have any questions, comments or suggestions, or would like further information about Complaints Statistics please email the <a href="mailto:NSS.isddvcomplaints@nhs.net">complaints mailbox</a></p>
     
